Custom prompt..

The prompt command allows you to put whatever information in your prompt
you want using the tokens below...

The cprompt command works in the same way but replaces the prompt command
during combat...

syntax: prompt [prompt str]
syntax: cprompt [prompt str]

If prompt/cprompt has no arguments it will revert your prompt to default.

Tokens..

%h - Hit points,   %H - Maximum Hit points
%m - Mana,         %M - Maximum Mana
%v - Movement,     %V - Maximum Movement
%x - Experience,   %g - Current Gold
%a - Alignment,    %r - Current room name
%T - Current mob fighting name
%t - Current mob fighting Hit points

So... the default prompt would be

prompt %hhp %mm %vmv>  
